On 10/22/2012 3:20 AM, Evan Tuer wrote:
> On Sun, Oct 21, 2012 at 10:22 PM, Chris Tromley<ctromley@gmail.com>  wrote:
>
>>
>> All good points, which leads me to wonder why there isn't a system that
>> offers both options.  Have a narrow band in the pedal travel that applies
>> no power and no regen.
>
> All the cars I've driven with regen do this..  It would be hard to see
> how else it would work!

The Prius accelerator pedal has a very narrow band between driving and 
regen where it coasts. But it is incredibly small, and cannot be felt. 
The only way to find it is by watching the "energy" display on the dash, 
to find the precise position where the ICE is off and the battery is 
neither being discharged nor charged (regen).

